---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "agents-setup")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn Claude`} currentId="agents-setup">
  <main>
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson} hero="agents">
      <p>Worked example: <strong>Hermes Agent</strong>. Two paths — pick one.</p>

      <h2>Path A · Claude Code plugin</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.9rem;">Easiest if Claude Code is already installed.</p>
      <pre>/plugin marketplace add sypsyp97/claude-hermes
/plugin install claude-hermes@claude-hermes
/claude-hermes:start</pre>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.9rem;">Wizard asks for: model, heartbeat, Telegram/Discord bots, security pin.</p>

      <h2>Path B · Standalone (curl)</h2>
      <pre>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/main/scripts/install.sh | bash
echo "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-…" &gt;&gt; ~/.hermes/.env
hermes model</pre>

      <h2>What you get</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Persistent.</strong> Lives in the background; remembers across sessions.</li>
        <li><strong>Scheduled.</strong> "Every Monday at 9, scan my inbox."</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-channel.</strong> Terminal, Telegram, Discord, voice.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>OpenClaw (same shape)</h2>
      <pre>npm install -g openclaw
openclaw init
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-…
openclaw run</pre>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.9rem;">
        See <a href="https://docs.openclaw.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">docs.openclaw.ai</a> for the current install.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Safety.</strong> Set a spend cap on your Anthropic account. Sandbox the workspace on first run.
        Read the diffs. Rotate the key if exposed.
      </div>
    </LessonShell>
  </main>
</Layout>
